# Tier-3 owner routing for the blast-radius merge automation.
#
# CODEOWNERS *syntax*, but DELIBERATELY NOT the magic `CODEOWNERS` filename — so
# GitHub does NOT auto-request these owners as reviewers. The bots resolve
# ownership from here: auto-assign assigns the Tier-3 owner; merge-policy requires
# the assignee's approval (falls back to any owner on the matched line when
# unassigned). Any ONE listed owner's approval satisfies the gate.
#
# RULES:
#   - Every entry MUST classify Tier 3 under config.yml (config.validate.test.ts
#     enforces this — an owner on a lower-tier path is an "orphan" and fails CI).
#   - List owners in priority order: `path @primary @backup` (OOO-aware).
#   - LAST-MATCH-WINS — list narrower sensitive paths after broader ones.
#
# >>> SCAFFOLDED STARTER — REPLACE @your-team WITH REAL HANDLES. <<<

# --- DevEx: the automation + CI that grades every PR (self-protecting) ---
/.github/workflows/        @your-team
/.github/blast-radius/     @your-team
/.github/prompts/          @your-team
/CODEOWNERS                @your-team

# --- EDIT: route your repo's Tier-3 paths to their owners ---
/src/auth/**               @your-team
/migrations/**             @your-team
/packages/*/src/index.ts   @your-team
